All four lines printed as expected. Here's a summary of the two APIs:

| API | What it does |
|---|---|
| `options.GetTypeInfo<T>()` | Returns `JsonTypeInfo<T>` directly — no cast needed. Throws if metadata isn't available. |
| `options.TryGetTypeInfo<T>(out JsonTypeInfo<T>?)` | Returns `bool`; populates the `out` param on success, returns `false` (no exception) on failure. |

The key lines in the demo:

```csharp
// Strongly-typed retrieval
JsonTypeInfo<Person> personInfo = options.GetTypeInfo<Person>();

// Safe probe (no try/catch needed)
if (options.TryGetTypeInfo<Person>(out JsonTypeInfo<Person>? info)) { ... }
```

Both are new generic overloads on `JsonSerializerOptions` in .NET 11, sitting alongside the existing non-generic `GetTypeInfo(Type)` / `TryGetTypeInfo(Type, out JsonTypeInfo?)`.
